PayCraft API Ecosystem

PayCraft aims to be a developer-first payment engine for Africa, inspired by Stripe but tailored to local realities. To achieve this, it needs a robust set of APIs that cover the full payment lifecycle, compliance, and developer experience.

üîë Core API Categories

1. Payments API

Purpose: Handle transaction flows (cards, mobile money, bank transfers).

Functions: Initiate charges, refunds, reversals, split payments.

How it works: Abstracts complex integrations with banks, card networks, and mobile money providers.

2. Payouts/Disbursement API

Purpose: Send money to vendors, gig workers, or partners.

Functions: Schedule payouts, bulk disbursements, status tracking.

How it works: Automates sending funds to multiple recipients across local rails.

3. Wallets & Accounts API

Purpose: Manage virtual accounts or wallets.

Functions: Create wallets, transfer funds, balance inquiry.

How it works: Acts as a ledger, enabling businesses to hold and move funds before settlement.

4. Identity & KYC API

Purpose: Verify users and businesses for compliance.

Functions: ID verification, business registration checks, AML screening.

How it works: Integrates with government or third-party verification services.

5. Developer Tools API

Purpose: Enhance developer experience.

Functions: Webhooks, sandbox/test environments, API keys & authentication.

How it works: Provides smooth DX with test environments and event-driven integrations.

6. Analytics & Reporting API

Purpose: Provide insights into transactions.

Functions: Transaction history, settlement reports, fraud detection signals.

How it works: Enables businesses to build dashboards and automate reconciliation.

7. Integration APIs (Local Rails)

Purpose: Connect PayCraft to Africa‚Äôs fragmented payment ecosystem.

Examples: Mobile money (M-Pesa, Airtel Money), bank APIs, card networks.

How it works: Acts as a unified layer, simplifying integrations.

‚öôÔ∏è How They Work Together

Payments API moves money in.

Payouts API moves money out.

Wallets API holds money in between.

Identity API ensures compliance.

Analytics API provides visibility.

Developer Tools API makes integration easy.

Integration APIs connect to local rails.

Together, they form a Stripe-like backbone tailored for Africa.

üåç Additional Considerations

Compliance & Regulation

PCI-DSS for card payments.

Local central bank approvals.

AML/CFT compliance frameworks.

Security

End-to-end encryption.

Tokenization of card data.

Role-based access control.

Developer Experience (DX)

SDKs in popular languages (Python, Node.js, Java).

Clear documentation with code samples.

Sandbox environments for testing.

Scalability & Reliability

Cloud-native architecture.

High availability with failover.

Real-time monitoring and logging.

Future APIs

FX & Currency Conversion API: Handle multi-currency payments.

Subscription/Billing API: Manage recurring payments.

Fraud Detection API: AI-driven risk scoring.

Open Banking API: Leverage bank data for smarter payments.

üöÄ Vision

PayCraft‚Äôs API ecosystem is designed to:

Empower African businesses with seamless, developer-first tools.

Bridge local payment rails into a unified platform.

Provide global-level reliability while staying proudly African.

This API-first approach ensures PayCraft is not just a payment processor, but a financial infrastructure layer for Africa‚Äôs digital economy.
